snippet.title: Pre-Algebra 18 - Converting Fractions to Decimal Numbers
snippet.description: Any fraction can be converted into an equivalent decimal number with a sequence of digits after the decimal point, which either repeats or terminates. The reason can be understood by close examination of the number line.
